{"id":"math120-limit_sub210-001","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Limits","subtopic":"Limits by direct substitution","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Evaluate the limit by direct substitution: lim (x to {c_val}) of ({a}x^2 + {b}x + {d}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"b":{"type":"int","min":-4,"max":4},"d":{"type":"int","min":-5,"max":5},"c_val":{"type":"int","min":-2,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"limit_sub210","steps":["Since the function is a polynomial, substitute x = {c_val} directly.","= {a}({c_val})^2 + {b}({c_val}) + {d} = {ac2} + {bc} + {d} = {answer_limit_sub210}."],"tags":["survey-calculus","limits","substitution"]}
